IT is one year that everybody wants to forget quickly - 2020! A year that has brought about change to the world, in every aspect of livelihood. And sport was also not sparred all the wrath of Covid-19, which saw games being halted for almost a year. This was a loss of income for thousands of people, loss of jobs and business suffered the most. Though games are back on, but there are very strict restrictions where fans are still not allowed to attend matches in the PSL. But the new normal included sport equipment being sanitised or decontaminated for the safety of all in order not contract the deadly virus. Let's relive the moments when football equipment was sanitised to protect athletes and officials, respectively.  